     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022; Completion of milestone 2 deliverables by Unitech Products (BD) Ltd., Elite Hi-Tech Industries Ltd., AC Bazar Industry, Supreme Air Conditioning, Cooling Point Engineering Services and Walton Hi-Tech Industries Ltd: R-290/R-32 technology acquisition which will be covered with the layout plan of civil, electrical and mechanical works as well as installation of equipment making pathway in phase-out of 17.09 ODP ton HCFC-22 by 2025.
&#x2022; Completion of milestone 3 deliverables by Unitech Products (BD) Ltd., Elite Hi-Tech Industries Ltd., AC Bazar Industry, Supreme Air Conditioning, Cooling Point Engineering Services and Walton Hi-Tech Industries Ltd: Plant modifications at least commensurate with the phaseout of agreed R-22 to R-290 (upto 1.5TR) and R-32 (above 1.5TR) inter alia 
o Installation 
o Commissioning
o Development of new standard operating procedures in the plant handing HC-290/R-32
o Phasing out of HCFCs
&#x2022; Completion of milestone 4 deliverables by Unitech Products (BD) Ltd., Elite Hi-Tech Industries Ltd., AC Bazar Industry, Supreme Air Conditioning, Cooling Point Engineering Services and Walton Hi-Tech Industries Ltd: Production trials at least commensurate with the phase-out of agreed R-22 to R-290 (upto 1.5TR) and R-32 (above 1.5TR) inter alia covering 
o Prototypes/samples
o Product certification
o Training of plant operators for operation of new line
o Safety audit/certification
&#x2022; Organizing two PIC meeting on project progress and incorporating feedback in the implementation of the project.
&#x2022; Organizing two PSC meeting of the project and incorporating feedback in the implementation of the project.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022; PMU has conducted field visits to monitor the progress of the six companies. Milestone one was completed by six companies and fund has been disbursed. Four companies have completed milestone two deliverable and fund has been disbursed.
&#x2022; National consultant &#x2013; design and safety has been recruited and has started working with the six companies. Field visits in six companies is finished to assess design and safety requirements.
&#x2022; Organized one PIC meeting on project progress and incorporating feedback in the implementation of the project.
&#x2022; Organized one PSC meeting on project progress and incorporating feedback in the implementation of the project.
&#x2022; HPMP Stage II project was selected for FAPAD Audit 2021 by the Government of Bangladesh. The audit was completed on the 2 March 2022. Preparation for the exit meeting of FADAP audit based on the issues raised by the audit team
&#x2022; The project conducted dedicated meetings with the six companies to discuss about their conversion progress and milestones two deliverables as per the MOA. 
&#x2022; The project has initiated the process for Tranche 2 request to MLF</narrative>
      </comment>
